ize=1> I decided that I would try to see exactly how many people would fall for that &quot;I just want to see what I look like wearing *X* item,&quot; so I made a new Gnome Warrior, named Gnomezzillah.  After about an hour I made it to level 3, then got ported to West Commons.  I then went to East Commons because I know billions of bored auctioning people would be at the tunnel, where I could ask them to try things on.  I started small, asking to try on a RyGorr Tunic here, see what an Executioner's Axe looks like there.  I even convinced a newbie to let me try on her Flowing Black Robe, even though I couldn't wear it as a Warrior.  I then gave everything back so people wouldn't think I was a scammer.<br><br>After being asked for SOW (um...is there a gnome class that can cast SOW?)  I asked a level 34 warrior in full crafted if I could try it on, because &quot;I never seen a gnome in plate before!!!&quot;  and when another gnome warrior ran by in Fine Plate, &quot;I never seen a gnome in BLUE plate before!!!&quot;  So he was hesitant and said that he would let me try it on, but he didn't know me, and that since I was only level three, he coudln't be sure that I wouldn't just keep it and log off without a reputation.<br><br>So then I said that I had been playing for 2 days, and that for me, level 3 was an accomplishment and that I would never do anything that would force me to have to start over.  Then the newbie said that I could be trusted, because she lent me her robe and I gave it back.  So the warrior (who I'm very tempted to name but I guess its not very nice to make fun of someone) puts all his crafted in a backpack (how courteous of him) and gives it to me to try on.  <br><br>So then I run around the tunnel saying &quot;HAHAHAHHA&quot; and for about five minutes I refused to give it back.  So then he said he was going to petition a GM, but I said I didn't care because GM's never do anything.  Then I sat down like I was camping and he started to curse at me in tells.  <br><br>Three minutes later, i decided that I would start auctioning it.  So I auctioned a full set of visible crafted for 200 pp for the set, and someone who happened to be sitting next to me said that they would buy it.  So he was getting really upset and I took off all the crafted and put it back in his backpack and told him I sold it, but that was ok because now I could buy us BOTH a set of banded.  LOL<br><br>Then he sat down and said he was sad and was camping, and to just keep the 200 pp because I just ruined what took him a year to earn.  So then I gave him his stuff back cause I would have felt really bad if I actually kept it.  He wasn't pleased that I had scammed him but he said that he was never going to let gnomes try on anything ever again.<br><br>At least he learned his lesson.  I have done my good deed of the month.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>My main's name is Angello, lv 51 Rogue by the way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utelly003.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telly003</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#E9D756>(12/19/01 11:55:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrscammeralert.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=299.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Scamming Experiment</span><hr size=1> Sorry, I see no humor in being mean.  You call it an experiment, but I bet the Warrior felt harassed, and rightfully so.<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uxargylex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xargylex</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezbo